com.ibm.mobile.services.cloudcode

Class IBMCloudCode

  • java.lang.Object
    • IBMBluemixService
      • com.ibm.mobile.services.cloudcode.IBMCloudCode

  • public final class IBMCloudCode
extends IBMBluemixService
    The IBMCloudCode class is a provisional API. APIs that are marked provisional are evolving and might change or be removed in future releases. The IBMCloudCode provides API to make cloud code invocations. initializeService() must be called before calling any other methods.

      • setBaseUrl

        public void setBaseUrl(java.lang.String baseUrl)
        A property that allows targeting a local Node installation while still leveraging other Mobile Cloud Services (e.g. IBM Data Service or IBM Push). This makes testing Cloud Code easier as it can be done while targeting a local Node server.
        Parameters:
        baseUrl - The URL of that should be used by the IBMCloudCode API when making HTTP requests.
